This paper discusses the use of context in neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning models, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the evaluation of NMT output, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of context in image captioning, which could suggest cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
